## Quartiles and the Interquartile Range (IQR)

Imagine you have 100 people sorted by height from shortest to tallest.
You split them into **4 equal groups of 25**. Each group is called a **quartile**.

```
|---Q1---|---Q2---|---Q3---|---Q4---|
  25%       25%      25%      25%
  ↑                           ↑
1st Quartile              3rd Quartile
(25th percentile)         (75th percentile)
```

- **Q1 (1st quartile)** = value where 25% of data is below
- **Q2 (2nd quartile)** = the median (50% below)
- **Q3 (3rd quartile)** = value where 75% of data is below
- **IQR (Interquartile Range)** = Q3 − Q1 = the range of the **middle 50%** of your data

> 💡 **Why is IQR useful?**
> It tells you how spread out the "typical" values are — ignoring extreme outliers.

