# Key Formulas

## IQR Formula
```
IQR = Q3 - Q1
```

## Outlier Boundaries (used in boxplots)
```
Lower boundary = Q1 - 1.5 × IQR
Upper boundary = Q3 + 1.5 × IQR

Any point outside these boundaries is shown as an outlier (dot) in the boxplot.
```

